mporary continental thought in a wide-ranging work that engages the philosophical problems of authenticity, self-appropriation, ethics, and the human subject.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Christianity. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / General.2bisacsh1 aCaputo, John D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoorley, Mark J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoorley, Mark J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJamieson, Christine E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanaris, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanaris, Jim, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLawrence, Frederick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarsh, James L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMckinney, Ronald H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlants, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaracino, Michele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791484319423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791484319/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles